@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
title Stateful contract by consume-and-recreate

participant "Off-chain builder" as B
participant "Script UTXO\n(old datum)" as OLD
participant "Validator\n(pure function)" as V
participant "Script UTXO\n(new datum)" as NEW

B -> OLD : reference by (TxId, index)\nas an input, with a redeemer
B -> B : construct tx: also create a\nnew output at the same address\nwith the updated datum
B -> V : submit
V -> V : check datum + redeemer + context
V -> V : does the tx recreate this\nscript address with a valid\nnext-state datum?
alt all conditions hold
  V --> NEW : approve; old UTXO consumed,\nnew state UTXO created
else any condition fails
  V --> B : reject atomically; no state change
end
note over OLD, NEW
  There is no in-place update. State moves
  forward by destroying one UTXO and
  creating its successor.
end note
@enduml
